00:44:15.450 --> 00:44:18.930
talk, to meet, to have
educational events.

00:44:18.930 --> 00:44:24.680
So the total flight may take
about two to three months.

00:44:24.680 --> 00:44:29.820
AUDIENCE: How much energy does
the plane use in flight?

00:44:29.820 --> 00:44:32.290
What would be the equivalent
chemical energy

00:44:32.290 --> 00:44:34.160
in gallons per hour?

00:44:34.160 --> 00:44:37.700
ANDRE BORSCHBERG: We are not
so used with using fuel, so

00:44:37.700 --> 00:44:40.140
it's in translation, which
is difficult to make.

00:44:40.140 --> 00:44:44.360
But if you talk about kilowatts
or horsepower, but I

00:44:44.360 --> 00:44:50.870
mean what our kilowatts are, the
power we use for the night

00:44:50.870 --> 00:44:54.140
flight, it's about
8 kilowatts.

00:44:54.140 --> 00:45:00.230
so if you multiply this by 24,
you get, more or less, the

00:45:00.230 --> 00:45:04.770
energy, plus, I guess, what you
lose in climbing and in

00:45:04.770 --> 00:45:06.670
going down.

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:11.700
You get something like 240
kilowatt hours, which is the

00:45:11.700 --> 00:45:15.510
total energy we collect and we
use over 24 hours with the

00:45:15.510 --> 00:45:16.966
first airplane.

00:45:16.966 --> 00:45:19.470
BERTRAND PICCARD: When the
batteries are full, we have 85

00:45:19.470 --> 00:45:21.210
kilowatt hours at
our disposal.

00:45:24.620 --> 00:45:27.530
ANDRE BORSCHBERG: So this 240,
that's about a third for

00:45:27.530 --> 00:45:31.400
battery, a third for flying,
and a third for climbing.

00:45:31.400 --> 00:45:32.950
BERTRAND PICCARD: But it's clear
that the challenge to

00:45:32.950 --> 00:45:34.890
have batteries rather
than kerosene.

00:45:34.890 --> 00:45:36.390
Is very high.

00:45:36.390 --> 00:45:40.240
Because one pound of kerosene
gives you the same energy than

00:45:40.240 --> 00:45:43.770
35 pounds of batteries.

00:45:43.770 --> 00:45:48.760
So it's absolutely clear that
kerosene is the most efficient

00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:50.560
way to fly--

00:45:50.560 --> 00:45:53.360
on the short term.

00:45:53.360 --> 00:45:53.950
ANDRE BORSCHBERG:
It's efficient.

00:45:53.950 --> 00:45:58.230
But the transformation of this
type of energy into propulsion

00:45:58.230 --> 00:46:01.100
energy, of course,
is much worse.

00:46:01.100 --> 00:46:04.503
So this ratio of 1 to 35
translates to something like 1

00:46:04.503 --> 00:46:08.310
to 10 if you see how efficient
electric motors are and how

00:46:08.310 --> 00:46:12.270
inefficient thermal engine is.

